      "_id": "R3NlcpoHzvsOeEl0",
      "name": "Noxious Miasma",
      "type": "feat",
      "img": "icons/svg/aura.svg",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>Constituição Teste de Resistência: DC 17, cada criatura in a 20- foot-radius Sphere centered on a point the dragon can see within 90 feet. Falha: 7 (2d6) Veneno de dano, and o alvo takes a -2 penalty to :,,: AC until the end of its next turn. Falha ou Sucesso: The l/1 0 dragon can't take this action again until the start of its l/1 0 next turn . z Pounce. The dragon moves -up to half its Speed, and it _J makes one Rend attack. ADULT GREEN DRAGON The words of adult green dragons are as deadly as their poisonous breath. They are brilliant schemers that pride themselves on influencing communities near their lairs. They obsess over information and create vast spy networks. Many of these dragons seek magical methods of surveillance or domina- tion, and they manipulate adventurers into hunting down lost magic to aid in such control. ANCIENT GREEN DRAGON Ancient green dragons are creatures of legend, rarely seen by their servants or foes. Via magic and well-hidden agents, these dragons stoke suspicion between allies and undermine noble works. As bonds fray, the dragons reap rewards of greater wealth and control. Eventually the ambitions of an- cient green dragons stretch beyond their territories as they seek control over empires, planar realms, or death itself. ANCIENT GREEN DRAGON Gargantuan Dragon (Chromatic), Lawful E1Ji! AC 21 Iniciativa+ 15 (25) HP 402 (23d20 + 161) . Speed 40 ft., Fly 80 ft., Swim 40 ft. MOD SAVE MOD SAVE MOD SAVE</p>",
          "chat": ""
